14/11/2002
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The Ministry of Defence announced Wednesday (13 November) that it will implement serious reforms in the army in line with the new Action Plan to prepare the country for NATO membership. According to the statement, the reforms will focus on reductions in the number of officers and civil servants. By 2007, the ranks would be trimmed by some 700 officers and 950 civilians.
In other news, Makfax reported Wednesday that representatives of international organisations expressed satisfaction with the conduct of Macedonia's ongoing census, and relief that no major incidents have been reported. Phase one of the count began on 1 November and will be completed Friday. (Dnevnik, MIA - 14/11/02; Makfax - 13/11/02)
